WEBVTT

00:03.141 --> 00:04.642
Come on!
Let's go.

00:04.727 --> 00:06.771
We're gonna need a little extra
time at airport security,

00:06.855 --> 00:09.148
'cause I'm pretty sure they're
gonna want to pat you down.

00:09.231 --> 00:11.693
Manny's with his father
for the weekend,

00:11.777 --> 00:14.363
so Jay and I
are flying to Vegas.

00:14.447 --> 00:17.451
I'm a little torn because
I want alone time with Gloria,

00:17.533 --> 00:20.537
but I also like rubbing
Manny's head for good luck.

00:20.621 --> 00:22.874
I just need to send
this e-mail to Claire...

00:22.956 --> 00:25.001
why I'm not working
on the bake sale next week,

00:25.085 --> 00:27.546
- but I can't say the real reason.
- Why not?

00:27.629 --> 00:30.759
Because she drive me crazy
when she's in charge of these things.

00:30.884 --> 00:33.637
We got a flight to catch, so let
me help you out here. Okay.

00:33.721 --> 00:37.725
You tell me what you wanna say to her,
and I'll help you find a nice way to say it.

00:37.808 --> 00:40.061
I want to say,

00:40.144 --> 00:41.689
“I can't work on the bake sale...

00:41.814 --> 00:44.192
because you're a bossy control freak-
[ Typing ]

00:44.275 --> 00:49.783
that looks down on my cupcakes, even though
your lemon squares were very dry.”

00:49.866 --> 00:52.159
[ Typing ]

00:52.244 --> 00:55.205
There. Okay?
How's this?

00:55.288 --> 00:58.084
“Dear Claire,
I can't work the bake sale...

00:58.167 --> 01:00.670
because you're a bossy
control freak who look down”-

01:00.754 --> 01:02.464
Very funny, Jay.

01:02.549 --> 01:04.551
[ Whooshing Sound ]
Ay. Ay.

01:04.634 --> 01:08.555
Why the whoosh? Where is-
Where is the e-mail? It sended!

01:08.639 --> 01:11.434
¡Ay! Make it come back.
I don't know how to make it come back.

01:11.518 --> 01:14.104
Now she's gonna read it
and she's gonna think it's from me!

01:14.187 --> 01:17.483
Well, technically, it was from you.
But come on. Let's hit the road.

01:18.567 --> 01:20.778
It sended!

01:22.948 --> 01:24.450
Please come back.

01:25.243 --> 01:33.252
♪ Hey, hey ♪

01:33.335 --> 01:34.629
♪ Hey ♪♪

01:37.090 --> 01:39.009
We love our neighborhood.
But sometimes,

01:39.092 --> 01:41.013
the last thing you wanna do
after fighting traffic...

01:41.096 --> 01:43.097
is get back in the car
to go out to eat,

01:43.180 --> 01:46.853
and the only restaurant
within walking distance is Shawarma City.

01:46.936 --> 01:49.315
Two shawarma combo.
Meat or chicken?

01:49.440 --> 01:52.901
One meat, one chicken.
And can you make the chicken all white meat?

01:52.985 --> 01:55.362
- Number 32. Pay cashier.
- That's not an answer.

01:55.447 --> 01:58.366
[Speaking Foreign Language]

01:59.327 --> 02:01.454
Then, a miracle happened.

02:01.537 --> 02:03.956
The hottest new restaurant In the city
opened up two blocks away

02:04.041 --> 02:06.335
Amelia's.
But there was a problem.

02:06.418 --> 02:09.045
- They can take us at 5:15.
- What are we, 80?

02:09.128 --> 02:11.383
- Or 10:45.
- What are we, 20?

02:11.467 --> 02:14.135
Then, miracle number two.

02:14.218 --> 02:18.934
Turns out one of the mothers at Lily's
preschool is none other than Amelia herself.

02:19.017 --> 02:21.186
So we arranged a playdate
with her son Jackson...

02:21.269 --> 02:23.148
where we would,
you know, charm Amelia.

02:23.231 --> 02:25.608
Okay. The most
important playdate ever.

02:25.691 --> 02:27.486
So I'm really gonna need you
to sparkle, sweetie.

02:27.569 --> 02:29.238
Oh, I'm gonna sparkle
like it's the Fourth of July.

02:29.322 --> 02:30.406
I was talking to Lily.
Hmm?

02:32.492 --> 02:36.288
It's our parents' anniversary, so we're
surprising them with breakfast in bed.

02:36.372 --> 02:38.707
They're impossible to buy for.

02:38.791 --> 02:41.545
We think.
We've never really tried.

02:44.297 --> 02:45.509
Okay, ready?

02:45.591 --> 02:48.052
One, two, three.

02:48.136 --> 02:49.137
[ Together]
Surprise-

02:49.221 --> 02:50.430
[All Screaming]
[ Dishes Crashing ]

02:50.514 --> 02:52.016
[Phil]
No! om

02:52.100 --> 02:53.560
[Claire] No! No!

02:53.644 --> 02:55.186
I'm sorry!
Nothing's happening!

02:55.270 --> 02:56.437
Oh, my God!

02:56.521 --> 02:58.358
Yeah. Our kids walked in on us.

02:58.441 --> 03:01.360
We were, as they say, having sex.

03:01.443 --> 03:04.532
That's not a euphemism, Phil.
It's exactly what we were doing.

03:04.615 --> 03:06.909
Having sex...
in front of our children.

03:06.993 --> 03:09.663
Well, they weren't there
when we started. No.

03:09.788 --> 03:13.041
In fact, you weren't even there
when we started. [ Inhales ]

03:13.125 --> 03:15.086
Oh, my God! Oh, my God!
It's okay.

03:15.211 --> 03:18.131
Maybe they didn't see anything.
Sweetie, they screamed.

03:18.215 --> 03:21.720
They dropped a tray of dishes and they
ran out of here like they were on fire.

03:21.803 --> 03:23.431
You were on fire, lady.

03:24.306 --> 03:25.807
Really? You're still going?

03:25.890 --> 03:29.062
Forgive me for thinking your zesty
performance deserves some praise.

03:29.187 --> 03:32.941
Phil, our children are downstairs right
now, and they're probably traumatized.

03:33.024 --> 03:35.361
Oh, come on.
I'm sure it's not that bad.

03:37.030 --> 03:38.156
I can still see it!

03:38.239 --> 03:39.909
I can't believe that just happened.

03:39.993 --> 03:41.911
What were they doing?
[Alex] Nothing.

03:41.995 --> 03:44.330
Whatever it was,
it looked like Dad was winning.

03:44.414 --> 03:46.751
“It”! They were doing “it”!

03:46.834 --> 03:49.211
- He has no idea what you're talking about.
- Sex?

03:49.295 --> 03:50.463
[ Haley]
Yes!

03:50.546 --> 03:52.299
I know what sex is, Alex.

03:52.382 --> 03:55.594
It's when a man and a woman take off their
underpants and then get into the bed.

03:55.677 --> 03:58.015
- Stop talking!
- [ Groans ]

03:59.475 --> 04:02.019
Try Claire again.
I'm not getting a signal.

04:02.102 --> 04:03.813
Relax. We'll get her.

04:04.939 --> 04:07.108
Shorty told me
about this restaurant in Vegas.

04:07.192 --> 04:10.614
It's got a three-story wine tower
right in the middle of it.

04:10.697 --> 04:14.033
Guy who gets your wine
flies around on a wire.

04:14.117 --> 04:15.620
Like the Peter Pan?
No.

04:15.703 --> 04:18.456
Not like “the Peter Pan.”
This is a high-end place.

04:18.540 --> 04:21.043
Oh, yeah, because
all the finest restaurants in the world...

04:21.125 --> 04:23.253
have people flying around
on wires.

04:23.378 --> 04:27.426
You know, you used to go bananas when the
Japanese guy flipped a shrimp onto your plate.

04:27.509 --> 04:29.511
- Now look at you.
- Try her again!

04:29.595 --> 04:31.889
Fine. And just so you know,
it's not like Peter Pan.

04:31.973 --> 04:33.683
I mean, nobody
wears tights or anything.

04:33.767 --> 04:36.479
Well, if they're not wearing anything,
I don't want them flying over my food.

04:36.561 --> 04:38.022
- [ Line Rings]
- [ Phil] Hello ?

04:38.104 --> 04:40.274
Phil, it's me.
Can I talk to Claire?

04:40.358 --> 04:41.819
Yeah. One second, Jay.

04:41.901 --> 04:44.029
It's your dad.
No. No, no. Can't. Uh-uh.

04:44.113 --> 04:45.614
She doesn't want to talk
right now.

04:45.698 --> 04:47.157
Ay, no.
Why not?

04:47.241 --> 04:49.369
Uh, she's a little too upset.

04:49.453 --> 04:51.831
Phil, put her on.

04:51.913 --> 04:54.375
He says he wants you-
Hang up the phone.

04:54.459 --> 04:56.502
- [ Gasps ]
- I'm sorry, Jay. She says I have to go.

04:56.586 --> 04:57.838
[ Groaning ]
[ Beeps ]

04:57.922 --> 05:00.465
You know, she's my daughter
and everything,

05:00.549 --> 05:03.762
but that guy seriously
needs to grow a pair.

05:03.846 --> 05:07.599
Well, we tried.
Vegas, here we come.

05:07.683 --> 05:10.062
Turn around the car.

05:12.439 --> 05:14.442
Only 'cause I want to.

05:20.116 --> 05:24.120
This is a beautiful home.
I love the throwback to the '60s.

05:24.204 --> 05:27.166
Although if this was the '60s,
we'd be a couple of “confirmed bachelors”...

05:27.249 --> 05:28.710
and Lily would be a Yorkie.

05:28.792 --> 05:31.004
[ Laughs ] And I'd still be
trapped in a loveless marriage.

05:31.088 --> 05:32.965
[ Laughing]
Oh, Amelia.

05:33.048 --> 05:34.591
Come on.
Oh, you are funny.

05:34.675 --> 05:37.053
[ Cameron ]
Oh!

05:37.137 --> 05:38.889
I really like you guys.

05:38.972 --> 05:41.516
I haven't had a lot of time
to meet the other parents.

05:41.600 --> 05:45.272
- Single mom, hectic work schedule-
- Now, what do you do, Amelia?

05:45.354 --> 05:47.149
I own a few restaurants.

05:47.231 --> 05:49.109
- Oh.
- I just opened one nearby.

05:49.193 --> 05:51.778
Oh, my gosh.
Are you that Amelia?

05:51.862 --> 05:54.324
- Mm-hmm.
- Oh, my gosh!

05:54.408 --> 05:57.287
We've heard wonderful things
about the restaurant. It must be doing well.

05:57.370 --> 05:59.955
We can never seem
to get a reservation.

06:00.039 --> 06:01.917
Can't get in.
Can't.

06:02.001 --> 06:04.711
Well, that's no problem.
The next time you call, just tell them-

06:04.795 --> 06:06.589
[ Ringing ]
Oop. One second.

06:06.673 --> 06:09.384
I'm sorry.
Tell them what? Hello?

06:09.468 --> 06:11.470
Did you show it to him?
And what did he say?

06:11.554 --> 06:15.224
Okay. Hold on a second.
I'm-I'm gonna switch phones.

06:15.351 --> 06:17.101
[Whispering ] I'm sorry.
It's the restaurant. Oh.

06:17.185 --> 06:20.982
- Excuse me just a minute.
- Yeah, you said to tell them something.

06:22.651 --> 06:24.778
Did you hear that?
When we know what to say, we're in.

06:24.862 --> 06:28.116
Oh, this is very exciting.
I've never had an in at a restaurant before.

06:28.200 --> 06:31.119
They'll probably greet us at the door by
our names, show us to our favorite table.

06:31.203 --> 06:32.788
Let us play fast and loose
with the menu,

06:32.872 --> 06:36.125
order lunch things for dinner,
dinner things for lunch.

06:36.209 --> 06:37.711
[ Gasps ]

06:37.794 --> 06:39.129
it's fine. it's fine. it's fine.

06:39.212 --> 06:40.756
Cameron, stop moving!

06:40.840 --> 06:43.385
[Amelia On Speaker] Are you there?
Put him on the phone.

06:43.467 --> 06:45.387
That's the baby monitor.
Should we turn it off?

06:45.471 --> 06:50.102
Who am I speaking to?
Well, Mr. Campbell,

06:50.185 --> 06:52.146
you need to replace
the extremely expensive countertop...

06:52.230 --> 06:54.482
that one of your incompetent workers
clearly ruined...

06:54.564 --> 06:56.527
when he was supposed to be
fixing the refrigerator.

06:56.610 --> 07:00.573
See? Okay. This is why she's so successful.
She's tough but calm.

07:00.657 --> 07:02.826
Because I'm not an idiot!

07:02.908 --> 07:04.744
As is evidenced by my law degree,

07:04.828 --> 07:08.123
which I will happily dust off and use
to crush you in court if you don't fix it,

07:08.207 --> 07:12.253
replace if or send me a check
in the next 72 hours.

07:12.337 --> 07:14.215
You know what?
Stay right here.

07:14.297 --> 07:15.675
Don't move.
[ Hangs Up ]

07:15.757 --> 07:18.219
- Act like you weren't listening.
- What does that look like?

07:18.303 --> 07:19.887
Like this.
[Amelia Groans]

07:19.972 --> 07:24.184
I'm so sorry. I have to run
down to the restaurant for a minute.

07:24.268 --> 07:27.772
I really feel terrible asking,
but would you guys mind?

07:27.856 --> 07:29.983
It's not a problem. We'll watch the kids.
[Cameron ] Oh, yes.

07:30.067 --> 07:33.864
You go take care of that fabulous restaurant
of yours that we cannot wait to try.

07:33.946 --> 07:35.867
And when we do call, Amelia,
you said-

07:35.949 --> 07:40.205
Jackson, Mommy will be right back, okay?
Thanks you guys so much.

07:40.289 --> 07:42.791
I owe you big-time.
Okay.

07:45.961 --> 07:48.882
- Did you hear that?
- She owes us big-time.

07:48.966 --> 07:50.926
You know, she also has
that restaurant in Las Vegas...

07:51.010 --> 07:53.138
where the sommeliers
fly around on wires.

07:53.220 --> 07:57.935
Oh, my gosh. Lily, thank you for being
such a trouper with Mr. Personality over there.

07:58.019 --> 08:00.146
I'm gonna get you a treat.

08:00.228 --> 08:02.900
Oh. A juice box broke in here.
It's all wet inside.

08:02.982 --> 08:03.984
[ Gasps ]

08:04.068 --> 08:06.780
Will you stop gasping?
It's just a diaper-

08:06.862 --> 08:09.950
[ Gasps ]
Oh!

08:14.081 --> 08:16.249
Okay. We need a game plan.

08:16.333 --> 08:18.336
We need to rehearse
exactly what we're gonna say,

08:18.418 --> 08:20.337
'cause that is the only way
I'm gonna hold it together...

08:20.421 --> 08:23.217
when my babies are looking at me
with judgment and disgust.

08:23.299 --> 08:25.761
First of all, that's how
they always look at us.

08:25.843 --> 08:27.846
Oh, Phil.

08:27.930 --> 08:30.182
Secondly, this isn't
as traumatic as you think.

08:30.267 --> 08:32.268
Honey, I walked in
on my parents having sex once.

08:32.352 --> 08:35.773
It was- oh, awful.
I can't even get the image out of my mind.

08:35.856 --> 08:38.275
Claire, we're not your parents.
We're in much better shape.

08:38.360 --> 08:41.114
Okay. You wanna know
the worst thing?

08:41.197 --> 08:43.534
They didn't even talk about it.
They just let it hang there.

08:43.616 --> 08:45.953
I'm not gonna do that
to our kids.

08:46.035 --> 08:49.958
Phil, this- this is a defining moment
for us as parents.

08:50.041 --> 08:52.585
How we handle this
could shape how they feel...

08:52.670 --> 08:54.921
about sex and intimacy for the
rest of their lives. Honey. Honey.

08:55.004 --> 08:57.551
- Ch, God.
- This is only a big deal if we make it a big deal.

08:57.634 --> 09:00.263
We set the tone here.
So let's just play it cool.

09:00.346 --> 09:03.223
Act like it was a big, funny mix-up.
Crack a few jokes, lighten the mood.

09:03.307 --> 09:05.434
Jokes?
Yeah.

09:05.519 --> 09:07.979
- What kind of jokes?
- Well, this is-

09:08.063 --> 09:10.483
I'm just spitballing here, but-
[ Clears Throat]

09:10.566 --> 09:12.776
What if I was all,
“Knock, knock.”

09:12.860 --> 09:14.738
And they were, like, “Who's there?”
And I was all,

09:14.821 --> 09:17.115
“Someone who doesn't want to see
their parents doing it.

09:17.199 --> 09:18.659
That's why we knocked.”

09:18.743 --> 09:22.039
[ Chuckles ]
Again, this is- this is very rough.

09:22.122 --> 09:23.832
Why are they still up there?

09:23.915 --> 09:26.127
Yeah. How long does sex take?

09:26.210 --> 09:28.255
Oh, my God.
Stop talking.

09:28.338 --> 09:32.759
Did you guys notice that Dad had the same
look on his face as when he smells a new car?

09:35.013 --> 09:37.682
I need to leave.
I need to go to camp.

09:37.766 --> 09:39.852
This is gonna be so weird
when they come down.

09:39.936 --> 09:42.313
Let's just go. Okay?
Come on.

09:43.482 --> 09:45.650
- Wait. But I'm hungry.
- We'll get breakfast.

09:45.735 --> 09:48.112
Let's just go! Come on!

09:48.196 --> 09:51.032
Let's go! Come on!
Where are you going?

09:51.116 --> 09:53.036
Anywhere.
Where is your mother?

09:53.118 --> 09:55.831
I need to talk to her.
I don't think it's a good time right now.

09:55.914 --> 09:57.166
She won't come out of her room.

09:57.249 --> 10:00.629
She's really upset, isn't she?
Big-time.

10:00.711 --> 10:02.923
How'd you know?
We called.

10:03.005 --> 10:04.592
Tell me exactly what she said.

10:04.674 --> 10:06.886
I don't know.
There was just a lot of screaming.

10:06.968 --> 10:09.223
Where was your father
when all this was going on?

10:09.305 --> 10:11.183
Oh. He was right behind her.

