13:10.862 --> 13:11.863
Phil.

13:17.537 --> 13:19.456
Good thing we had
Mom's gas card.

13:19.540 --> 13:22.168
Don't make me regret
buying you that lighter, dude.

13:22.252 --> 13:24.837
Put it down.
Okay, I'm just gonna say it.

13:24.922 --> 13:26.923
Our parents are totally irresponsible.

13:27.008 --> 13:30.761
And I'm not just talking about us
walking in on their little freak show earlier.

13:30.846 --> 13:34.141
Just let it go.
No! We're lucky to be alive.

13:34.224 --> 13:38.772
How often do they let Luke
go to school in shorts in the winter?

13:38.855 --> 13:41.566
And they let me ride in the front seat
before I was 60 pounds.

13:41.650 --> 13:45.739
And they never shut the gate
at the top of the stairs when we were babies.

13:45.821 --> 13:48.241
Do you know how many times
you fell on your head? Do you?

13:48.326 --> 13:51.288
No.
We get it. It was bad.

13:51.371 --> 13:52.915
But, you know,

13:52.997 --> 13:59.172
I guess it's better than having parents
who fight all the time... maybe.

13:59.255 --> 14:01.716
My friend Jacob's parents
are getting divorced.

14:01.800 --> 14:04.095
He has to move out of his house.

14:04.178 --> 14:08.476
They told him last week.
That sucks.

14:08.558 --> 14:11.478
He'll get used to it.
Half of my friends' parents are divorced.

14:11.562 --> 14:14.650
Mine too.
It's insane..

14:14.732 --> 14:18.655
So it's a good thing
Mom and Dad still do sex.

14:18.738 --> 14:22.785
Better than Mom leaving the stove on,
which she's done twice this month.

14:22.868 --> 14:25.996
