17:46.036 --> 17:47.496
Oh, my God. Oh, my God!

17:47.578 --> 17:49.372
We are horrible people.
I'm only following your lead.

17:49.456 --> 17:51.625
Yeah, so close that you stepped on
the back of my shoe.

17:51.709 --> 17:54.296
Come here. Jackson's allergic to strawberries.
His throat will close up.

17:54.378 --> 17:56.923
He can go into anaphylactic shock.
I need to inject him right now.

17:57.007 --> 17:59.802
He seems all right to me.
Maybe just get him some fresh air.

17:59.886 --> 18:01.721
Stop talking!
He really hates this,

18:01.805 --> 18:04.641
so I'm gonna need you to help me
pin down his arms and his legs.

18:04.724 --> 18:08.103
Jackson, Mommy's so sorry to have to do this,
but it's only gonna hurt for a second.

18:08.187 --> 18:09.688
His arms!
Oh!

18:09.773 --> 18:12.526
Okay. All right, here we go.
One. Two-

18:12.610 --> 18:14.195
Wait!
Wait!

18:14.320 --> 18:17.114
Jackson didn't drink the juice.
I stepped on Lily's bag. The juice box fell.

18:17.240 --> 18:19.994
We panicked because we heard you on the phone
and we can't afford Joan Collins's rug!

18:20.077 --> 18:21.912
We are so, so sorry.

18:21.996 --> 18:23.497
We could not feel any worse.

18:27.961 --> 18:30.382
Oh, no. That's bad.

18:30.464 --> 18:32.174
Number 19!

18:32.258 --> 18:35.179
Yeah. Yeah.
Number 19!

18:35.262 --> 18:36.764
Oh, could we have
some napkins, please?

18:36.848 --> 18:39.268
All out of napkins.
Paper towels in bathroom, Mitchell.

18:40.101 --> 18:42.437
He knows your name!

18:42.521 --> 18:44.273
[Claire]
And, uh, I'm just gonna say it.

18:44.357 --> 18:47.026
I'm really sorry
about what happened.

18:47.110 --> 18:49.406
Well, we're not sorry
about what happened.

18:49.531 --> 18:53.910
We're sorry that you saw what happened.
Okay. They get that.

18:53.995 --> 18:57.372
Let's see.
No one wants to see their parents-

18:58.499 --> 19:00.252
Sssssss-

19:00.334 --> 19:03.214
Your sensuality-
not dressed- Oh.

19:03.297 --> 19:06.467
Basically, it's two adults.
Adults.

19:06.552 --> 19:08.219
It's like you're shaking hands-
Mm-hmm.

19:08.304 --> 19:10.973
But you're not using
your hands at all.

19:11.057 --> 19:13.351
I can't handle
a big family talk about this.

19:13.434 --> 19:15.020
We're not gonna have a choice.

19:15.104 --> 19:19.232
When they start talking, just smile and nod
and think about something else.

19:19.318 --> 19:22.236
Yeah, it's easy.
Just like at school.

19:22.320 --> 19:23.990
Yeah.

19:24.072 --> 19:26.701
[Claire] So I guess
what I'm saying here is that...

19:26.783 --> 19:31.080
as you get older
and explore your sexuality,

19:31.165 --> 19:35.587
you will discover that as long as
you are in a committed relationship...

19:35.669 --> 19:38.757
with consenting adults, there's really
nothing to be embarrassed about.

19:38.841 --> 19:41.428
And let's face it. Your mom
can't keep her hands off me...

19:41.510 --> 19:43.388
whenever the gun show
comes to town.

19:43.471 --> 19:46.142
[ Laughing ]
Good one, Dad.

19:46.225 --> 19:49.188
Humor makes
difficult situations easier.

19:50.439 --> 19:51.690
Wow. Really?

19:51.774 --> 19:53.943
Totally.
You talked to us on our level,

19:54.027 --> 19:55.945
but without being condescending.

19:56.028 --> 19:58.657
We did.
All right.

19:58.741 --> 20:01.202
I guess we did.
Huh!

20:01.285 --> 20:02.913
Yay us!

20:02.995 --> 20:05.624
I think we really handled that well.
Me too.

20:05.706 --> 20:08.418
You were excellent.
You were pretty good.

20:08.503 --> 20:10.673
Oh!
Oh.

20:10.755 --> 20:13.384
This is such a weird day.
I know it.

20:13.466 --> 20:15.553
By the way, happy anniversary.

20:15.637 --> 20:18.723
It always is. Mmm.

20:18.806 --> 20:22.102
Hey, Mom, can I get-
